To ensure the network traffic analyzer could accurately capture data, the following virtualized environment was established:

Hypervisor: Oracle VirtualBox.

Host Operating System: Windows.

Guest Operating System: Ubuntu Linux.

Network Adapter: Bridged or NAT Network adapter linked to the host's Ethernet 7 interface.

Packet Capture Driver: Npcap (installed to resolve initial local interface unavailability).

Virtual IP Address: 192.168.1.192 (Ubuntu Guest).

External Target: 142.251.41.174 (Google Server).
